<TITLE> VIPs seek HC bail, Tarique's bail extended </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, January 27 (bdnews24.com)Former chief whip Abul Hasnat Abdullah, former communication minister Anwar Hossain Manju, Awami League leader Mofazzal Hossain Chowdhury Maya, BNP leader Shahjahan Siraj and Nadim Mostofa appeared before the High Court seeking bail in separate cases on Tuesday. A HC bench of justices Syed Mahmudul Haque and Mainul Islam Chowdhury heard bail applications by Abdullah and Manju. The court may pass orders on Wednesday after hearing bail applications of the other VIPs. All have been convicted and sentenced to different terms in separate cases. Barrister Rafique-ul-Haque, barrister Amir-ul-Islam and Barrister Rokanuddin Mahmud moved the applications for the VIPs. Tarique bail extended Meanwhile, the Supreme Court extended Tarique Rahman's bail for five months in a Tk 21 crore extortion case. A four-member bench of the Appellate Division, headed by chief justice M.M. Ruhul Amin, passed the order on an application by Tareque's lawyers. The SC granted him six months bail on Aug 2008 in the case involving bribery for an alleged cover-up of the murder of Bashundhara Group director Sabbir. Barrister Rafiqul Islam Mian moved the application for Tarique. 
